{"questionId":"22653","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Joey is making a party hat in the form of a cone. The hat is made from a sector, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AOB</mtext></math>, of a&nbsp;circular piece of paper with a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>18</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>AÔB</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>θ</mi></math> as shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/5e81add220ed385c485c31ef633086447f031dfa.png\"></p>\n<p>To make the hat, sides <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>[OA]</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>[OB]</mtext></math> are joined together. The hat has a base radius&nbsp;of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/f0d9ca5276788553bcd800ef1c8e8f6911136aae.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the perimeter of the base of the hat in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Answer must be in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.<br><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22653","referenceCode":"21N.1.SL.TZ0.8a.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the perimeter of the base of the hat in terms of π.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—The circle, arc and area of sector, degrees only"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}